This paper presents the design and development of an intelligent social robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The robot is equipped with features that can interpret and respond to users' emotions through facial expressions and spoken language, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study focuses on improving the quality of life of elderly individuals with dementia and depression, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a robot also involves cybersecurity concerns (cs.CYBER). Finally, the study involves analyzing the interactions between the robot and the elderly individuals, which could fall under the category of software development (cs.SD).
